Privacy Policy for Heffen Mobile App

Effective Date: 16 November 2023

At Heffen, we are committed to protecting your privacy and ensuring the security of any personal information you provide to us. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, and disclose information when you use the Heffen mobile application ("App").

Information We Collect
1.1 Verification Information: To ensure that users of Heffen are affiliated with Hong Kong University (HKU), we require users to provide their HKU email address. This email address is used solely for the purpose of sending a verification code to confirm that the user is an HKU student. We do not collect any other personal information during the verification process, and we do not use this information for any other purpose.

Use of Information
2.1 Non-Personal Information: We may use non-personal information collected through the App for various purposes, including but not limited to analyzing app usage patterns, improving the App's functionality and user interface, and troubleshooting technical issues.

2.2 Verification Information: The HKU email addresses collected for verification purposes are used solely to send the verification code and confirm the user's affiliation with HKU. We do not use this information for any other purpose, such as marketing or profiling.

Data Storage and Security
3.1 Data Storage: We store the non-personal information collected through the App on secure servers or cloud-based storage systems. The verification email addresses are stored temporarily only for the duration of the verification process.

3.2 Data Security: We take reasonable measures to protect the information collected through the App against unauthorized access, disclosure, alteration, or destruction. However, please note that no method of transmission over the internet or electronic storage is 100% secure, and we cannot guarantee its absolute security.

Disclosure of Information
4.1 Third-Party Service Providers: We may engage third-party service providers to perform certain functions necessary to operate and maintain the App. These service providers may have access to non-personal information solely for the purpose of providing their respective services to us and are obligated to maintain the confidentiality of the information.

4.2 Legal Requirements: We may disclose non-personal information if required to do so by law or in response to valid requests by public authorities (e.g., a court or government agency).

Children's Privacy
The Heffen App is not intended for use by individuals under the age of 13. We do not knowingly collect personal information from children under 13 years of age. If we become aware that we have collected personal information from a child under the age of 13, we will take steps to promptly delete that information.

Changes to this Privacy Policy
We reserve the right to update or modify this Privacy Policy at any time. If we make any material changes, we will notify you by email or by posting a notice on the App's website or within the App itself. Your continued use of the App after any such changes indicates your acceptance of the revised Privacy Policy.

Contact Us
If you have any questions or concerns about this Privacy Policy or our privacy practices, please contact us at service@heffen.app.

Please review this Privacy Policy carefully before using the Heffen App. By using the App, you acknowledge that you have read, understood, and agreed to be bound by this Privacy Policy.

Last updated: 16 November 2023


